definition: to come/to arrive/to come round/ever since/next

sentences.english: I like the early years of a winter snow.
sentences.chinese: 我喜歡今冬早來的一場雪。

sentences.english: I'll come early tomorrow in order to save your waiting.
sentences.chinese: 明天我會早來點兒，省得讓你等着。

sentences.english: Always arrive at work 30 minutes before your boss.
sentences.chinese: 總比你老闆早來30分鐘上班。

sentences.english: The students on duty always come early.
I came to the class early so that I could see the classmate beside me.
sentences.chinese: 我趕早來上課，以便早點看到我旁邊的同學。

sentences.english: I am the team member who reports early every morning and leaves last.
sentences.chinese: 在這個隊伍中，我每天都早來晚走。

sentences.english: Giles phoned this morning, " Mirella said with feigned indifference."
sentences.chinese: “賈爾斯今早來電話了，”米雷拉裝作若無其事地說。

sentences.english: A few minutes earlier, and you could have seen Hankyung.
sentences.chinese: 要是你早來幾分鐘，你就能見到韓庚了。

sentences.english: Hobbs came here this morning. He's very angry with you about that letter.
sentences.chinese: 彼得霍布斯今早來了，他對你的那封信很生氣。
